text: Timothée Hal Chalamet (born December 27, 1995) is an American-French actor. He has won several awards for his work. == Career == He became known after appearing in the drama series Homeland in 2014. Chalamet starred in Christopher Nolan's science-fiction movie Interstellar. In 2017, Chalamet starred in the romantic drama Call Me by Your Name. He has appeared in other films and television shows including Little Women. Chalamet also had leading roles in Dune and Wonka. In 2025, he was nominated for a Golden Globe Award for his role as Bob Dylan in A Complete Unknown (2024). == Personal life == Chalamet was born in New York to an American mother of Russian and Austrian Jewish descent and a French father. He lives in both New York and California. In 2023, it was reported that he was dating Kylie Jenner. ==Sources== Category:1995 births Category:Living people Category:Actors from New York City Category:American child actors Category:American movie actors Category:American stage actors Category:American television actors Category:American voice actors
